{"word":"σωτήριος","slug":"σωτήριος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>σωτήριος, ον</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:σωτήρ\">σωτήρ</a></el>] ‘<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pert. to\">pert. to</a> rescue’<b><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> of God’s beneficent favor <b>rescuing, bringing salvation <a href='B:630 2:11'>Tit 2:11</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> as noun <el>τὸ σωτήριον</el> the means whereby rescue/salvation takes place <b><a href='B:560 6:17'>Eph 6:17</a>;</b> specifically as God’s <el>σ.</el> <b><a href='B:490 2:30'>Lk 2:30</a>; <a href='B:490 3:6'>3:6</a>; <a href='B:510 28:28'>Ac 28:28</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:σωτηρία\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:σωφρονέω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}